This paper deals with information transmission over AWGN channels with a focus on low probability of detection. This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses practical scenarios and lower bounds on noise power, which could be relevant to multimedia (cs.MM), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and social and information networks (cs.SI) sub-categories.
